While Ingress defines the rules, the Ingress Controller is the actual implementation that enforces them.

Popular Ingress Controllers include:
 â€¢ NGINX Ingress Controller
 â€¢ Traefik
 â€¢ HAProxy
 â€¢ Istio Gateway (when using service mesh)
 â€¢ AWS ALB Ingress Controller (for EKS)

Without an Ingress Controller running in your cluster, Ingress resources wonâ€™t do anythingâ€”they're just config.

